at OHA have been using R and Python for analysis and reporting since before the pandemic. Efforts

00:06:53.119 --> 00:06:58.399
to modernize public health data systems and workflows over the last five years revealed

00:06:58.399 --> 00:07:06.720
common themes among analytic teams. Specifically, teams need transparent, reproducible, portable,

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:12.160
cost-effective solutions for informatics and automated reporting. And open source tools

00:07:12.160 --> 00:07:17.440
provide just that. Informatics teams have been eager to take on the challenge of incorporating

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:23.519
these tools into their work streams. Oregon received federal data modernization grant

